`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
These strings weren't `TODO`/`TBD`/`Lorem` — the audit flagged them because they read like HTML default UI hints ("Select an option" is a browser-native affordance, not intentional product copy). The fix: use ellipsis-terminated phrasings (`"Choose one…"`) and abbreviate where appropriate (`"reference no."`) to signal intentional authorship rather than generated defaults.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

